OL,3,CHow to avoid authorised push payment
OL,4,Cfraud as officials slash compensation
OL,6,FITV News Consumer Editor Chris Choi
OL,7,Fspoke to one fraud victim who lost
OL,8,Fmuch of her life savings
OL,10,FOfficials have reduced the amount of
OL,11,Fcompensation banks will pay to fraud
OL,12,Fvictims. Instead of covering #415,000
OL,13,Fof losses, only #85,000 will be
OL,14,Fcovered.
OL,16,FCampaigners representing bank
OL,17,Fcustomers say the move is an
OL,18,F"outrageous" watering down of scam
OL,19,Fprotections.
