OL,3,CHow to avoid authorised push payment
OL,4,Cfraud as officials slash compensation
OL,6,FAuthorised push payment fraud happens
OL,7,Fwhen someone is tricked into sending
OL,8,Fmoney to a fraudster posing as a
OL,9,Fgenuine payee.
OL,11,FBanking insiders at UK Finance have
OL,12,Fcalled it a "tide of criminal activity
OL,13,Ftargeting consumers" with there being
OL,14,Fa 12% rise in victims last year
OL,16,FIn December last year the sector's
OL,17,Fwatchdog, the Payment Systems
OL,18,FRegulator, said the level of mandatory
OL,19,Fcompensation would be #415,000 to
OL,20,Fmatch the upper level of awards from
OL,21,Fthe Financial Ombudsman.
